Supporters
In 2006 the Cincinnati Kings supporters founded a group dubbed 'The Pride', inspired by the lion in the club's crest. The dedicated group cheers on the Kings at every game with banners, flags, drums and chants. The Pride's crest has the message Juncta Juvant, which was inspired by the city of Cincinnati flag, which also has the message which means "Strength in Unity". The Pride can be found online at [https://www.myspace.com/ckfc_pride]
